//## HUMANOID ROBOT USING ESP32
//## OVERVIEW
    This project demonstrates a humanoid robot built using ESP32. 
    The robot performs basic human-like movements using servo motors, 
    detects obstacles using an ultrasonic sensor, and displays 
    information on an OLED display.
//## COMPONENTS WE HAVE USED
     ESP32 DevKit V1
     SG90 Servo Motors
     HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor
     OLED Display (SSD1306/SH1106)
     Jumper Wires
     Power Supply
//## LIBRARIES WE HAVE USED 
    SP32 DevKit V1
    SG90 Servo Motors
    HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor
    OLED Display (SSD1306/SH1106)
    Jumper Wires
    Power Supply
//## WHAT IT DOES
    Human-like movement using servo motors
    Obstacle detection using ultrasonic sensor
    OLED display for system status
    Wireless control using WiFi/Blynk
//## WHERE IT ALL STARTED     
    This project was created during a hackathon in our first year of engineering where 
we built a humanoid robot from scratch. Initially, we had limited knowledge about robotics,
but by exploring and learning during the event, we were able to successfully develop a working model.
The experience helped us gain practical knowledge in programming, electronics, and robotics. We also gained hands on experience.
